This paper deals with the problem of packet scheduling in an energy harvesting wireless communication system, which involves the optimization of transmission rate based on traffic load and available energy. This problem is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI), as well as system and control theory (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.MA), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
